cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the energy efficiency of cellular networks through relays, which is a networking topic. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the distributions of signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratios (SINRs) and mean achievable rates, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an analytical model to evaluate the energy efficiency of relay-assisted cellular networks, which can be considered a system. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the mean achievable rates of both non-cooperative users and cooperative users, which can be related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not explicitly discuss security, the use of relays in cellular networks can have implications for security and privacy, making this sub-category a possibility.
